The paper deals with the problem of simplifying closed curves in the plane, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of topological invariants and homotopy theory, which are related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SD (Systems and Control). The use of lower bounds and worst-case analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
